{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0073-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Structured Notes",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1740700800000,
  "modified": 1773334195800,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Status:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Merged into notes"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Summary"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Structured notes are now part of the regular note type. Any note can have "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.computed"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " fields and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{{field-name}}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " references in its "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.description"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Uses "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0074-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Reactive Computed Fields"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " as the single underlying mechanism — a transclusion is just a computed field whose formula mirrors another item's field. Notes without computed fields render exactly as before."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Unification"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The original version of this proposal introduced four Hob page primitives ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "text"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "transclude"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "val"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "link"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") and a new page format where pages are Hob expressions. Through iteration, a simpler insight emerged: all of these collapse into one mechanism — computed fields with "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-field"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " as uniform access."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "What you want"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "What it actually is"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Transclusion of another note"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(get-field @other-note :description)"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " — a computed field mirroring another item's field"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Inline computed value"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(* (get-field :self :quantity) (get-field :self :price))"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " — a computed field with logic"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Functional transclusion ("
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "?call="
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": ")"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(invoke (require \\\"module\\\") \\\"fnName\\\" api params)"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " — a computed field calling a module export"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Aggregation"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(reduce + 0 (map (fn [i] (get-field i :amount)) (query-tagged @expense-tag)))"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " — a computed field over a query"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "One mechanism. One reactive system. One way to track dependencies. No special transclusion primitives needed."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Note Structure"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Any note (type "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "871ae771-..."
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") can use computed fields:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "{\n  \"type\": \"871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"description\": \"Here is a summary: {{summary}}. The total budget is **{{total-budget}}**.\",\n    \"quantity\": 10,\n    \"unit-price\": 25.50,\n    \"computed\": {\n      \"summary\": [\"get-field\", \"@other-note\", \":description\"],\n      \"total-budget\": [\"*\", [\"get-field\", \":self\", \":quantity\"],\n                            [\"get-field\", \":self\", \":unit-price\"]]\n    }\n  }\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.description"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — markdown string with "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " references. Uses the standard note field."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.computed"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — map of field names to Hob formulas. Evaluated lazily via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "get-field"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". See "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0074-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Reactive Computed Fields"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Static fields ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "quantity"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "unit-price"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ") coexist alongside computed fields normally."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Authoring Experience"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The editor preserves the feel of writing a note:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Prose"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": type normally in CodeMirror — markdown, same as today."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Field references"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": insert "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " anywhere in the body to reference a named field (static or computed)."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Links"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": use existing "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item://id"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " syntax — unchanged."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Field management"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": a side panel or inspector for creating and editing computed fields — name, Hob formula, current value."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "One syntax, one concept: "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{{field-name}}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " always means \"resolve this field via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-field"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ".\" Whether the field is a transclusion, a calculation, or a static value is defined in the field itself, not in the body syntax."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Editor gestures"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Inserting a transclusion is two logical steps — create the computed field, then reference it — but the editor streamlines this into a single gesture: an \"insert transclusion\" action prompts for a target item and a field name, then creates both the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.computed"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " entry and the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{{name}}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " reference at the cursor."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Storage"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "What you see in the editor is what's stored. "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{{field-name}}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " in the body maps 1:1 to a key in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.computed"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (or a static field in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). No compilation step, no generated names, trivial round-tripping."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Rendering"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The note readonly view (a generic-view delegate) renders via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "field-view-markdown-readonly"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", which:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Detects "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " patterns in "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.description"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "For each reference, calls "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.getField(itemId, fieldName)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — a JS API that delegates to the Hob "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "get-field"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " function."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Wraps resolved values in "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "<span class=\\\"field-ref\\\">"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " with dashed underline styling and click-to-scroll behavior."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Renders the result as markdown via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "hobson-markdown"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A collapsible \\\"Fields\\\" section (rendered by "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "field-view-field-summary"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") shows:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Static fields as "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "name: value"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Computed fields with formula (via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "field-view-hob-structural"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "), resolved value, and provenance links to referenced items."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For notes without "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{{"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " references or computed fields, neither the ref resolution nor the field summary activates — rendering is identical to before."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Implementation Progress"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Completed"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Merged into note type"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Structured note capabilities are now part of the regular note type ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "871ae771-..."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "). The note readonly and editable views handle computed fields, static fields, and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " references."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`get-field` function"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " in the Hob interpreter: unified field access with computed field support. Resolves item refs, keywords, and string field names. Checks "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.computed"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for formulas, evaluates via Hob evaluator, falls back to item root then "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". Includes cycle detection via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "_computingFields"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Set."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`api.getField`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " on the rendering API: JS-callable wrapper around Hob "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "get-field"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", enabling field views and generic-view delegates to resolve computed fields without needing the Hob interpreter directly."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`resolve-field-refs`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " in Hob stdlib: resolves "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " references in a string using "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "get-field"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — used for cross-item body transclusion."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`field-view-markdown-readonly`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Updated to detect "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{field-name}}"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " patterns, resolve them via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.getField"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", wrap resolved values in clickable "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "<span class=\\\"field-ref\\\">"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " with dashed underline styling and click-to-scroll behavior. No effect on notes without "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " references."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`field-view-field-summary`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Readonly combined summary showing static fields and computed fields. Computed fields display formula (via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "field-view-hob-structural"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "), resolved value, and provenance links to referenced items (extracted via JSON AST walk)."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`field-view-computed-fields`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "e8d7c6b5-...-5c4e"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "): Editable field view rendering "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.computed"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " as name/formula pairs. Each formula edited via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "field-view-hob-structural"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". Supports add/remove/rename."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`field-view-static-fields`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "e8d7c6b5-...-5c4f"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "): Editable field view for arbitrary static content fields, with caller-specified "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "exclude"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " list."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`generic-view`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " updated: passes "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " to field views via options; skips field views that render as "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "display: none"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Provenance links"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Computed field formulas are walked (JSON AST) to extract "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "-prefixed item references. Each referenced item is displayed as a clickable link in the field summary, using "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.openItem"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for navigation.\\n- "
            },
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Functional transclusions"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Computed fields can call module exports that return DOM elements. "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "require"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " moved from view-only to stdlib (available in all Hob contexts). The rendering "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " is passed into the formula evaluation environment via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "_evalApi"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", so formulas can call "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(invoke (require \\\"module\\\") \\\"fn\\\" api params)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". DOM results are mounted into placeholder spans after markdown rendering.\\n- "
            },
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`require` in stdlib"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Moved from "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "registerViewOps"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " to "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "registerItemOps"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — now available in computed field evaluation, REPL, event handlers, not just views. Uses "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.require"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " from the kernel module system."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Known Limitations"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Cross-item reactivity"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": The view only re-renders when its own item changes. If a computed field references another item and that item changes, the view doesn't re-render. See "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0074-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Reactive Computed Fields"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for the assessment (~85 lines to fix)."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No caching"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Computed fields are re-evaluated on every access. Fine for current use; caching is a future optimization."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "No error sentinels"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": Formula errors are caught and shown as empty or "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "[error]"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". The proposal describes error items and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "ERR"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " links — not yet implemented (~40 lines). See "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0074-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
